Description: Handle sliver of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay fine buff-brown.
Production date: 124 BC (see N. Badoud, Le temps de Rhodes, 2015, 143.)
Curator's comments: Trimmed. Name Teisamenos. From same die as Crocodilopilis/Arsinoe KF569.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1147)
